                            <comment id="12708673" author="apurtell" created="Tue, 12 May 2009 23:01:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Example from my small test cluster&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;2009-05-12 22:59:46,226 INFO org.apache.hadoop.hbase.master.ServerManager: 3 region servers, 0 dead, average load 94.0&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12708689" author="stack" created="Tue, 12 May 2009 23:49:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I was thinking of doing something similar &amp;#8211; fools seldom differ &amp;#8211; but I was thinking it should be metrics based. What you think Andrew?  Then it&apos;d show in the UI and in ganglia too as well as in logs?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12708696" author="apurtell" created="Wed, 13 May 2009 00:12:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;How about add metrics stuff in addition? I can see a Chore in ServerManager being a useful place to drop in other stuff over time.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12708700" author="stack" created="Wed, 13 May 2009 00:23:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;sure; commit what you have and then we can add metrics.  I think it&apos;ll subsume how you currently calculate this stuff but we&apos;ll get to it when we get to it (smile).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12708702" author="apurtell" created="Wed, 13 May 2009 00:28:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed to trunk.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
